{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Simple agent network using a single LLM-based agent",
        "tags": ["example"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. The engines are stopped and wheelchocks are ready. Install the wheelchocks.", 
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        "model_name": "gpt-5.4-mini", #"gpt-4o", # "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001", #"claude-sonnet-4-6", #
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000, #3000 
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200, #600
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at an Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "wheelchocks_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
 I am in charge of installing wheelchocks to the aircraft at the gate.
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },         
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },        
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate where the aircraft is parked."
                        },       
                        "engines_stop_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of engines stop."
                        },     
                        "wheelchocks_installation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of wheels chocks installation."
                        },               
                        "wheelchocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheelchocks readiness status."
                        },   
                    }, 
                    "required": ["aircraft_type","gate_id"] 
                }
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent in charge of installing wheelchocks to the aircraft at the gate.  
When user submit inquiry to install wheelchocks, proceed as follows: 
1. Read the inquiry and determine if it is about wheelchocks installation. 
    a. If not, reply that you are not relevant to this inquiry and stop process here. 
    b. If it is about wheelchocks installation, continue to step 2.
2. Call "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_wheelchocks_setup" to verify wheelchocks readiness status as wheelchocks_readiness_status with aircraft_type and gate_id 
    a. wait for its response and store wheelchocks_readiness_status from the response
    b. If wheelchocks_readiness_status is not explicitly confirmed as 'ready' or 'yes', return to user that wheelchocks is not ready and can not be installed, and stop process here.
3. If wheelchocks_readiness_status is 'ready' or 'yes', find the following parameters from the inquiry: 
    a. flight status as flight_status with value such as 'on blocks', 
    b. engines stop status as engines_stop_status with value such as 'stopped' or 'running',
4. If flight_status is not 'on blocks' or engines_stop_status is not 'stopped', 
    a. call TrackerAPI
    a. wait for its response 
    b. store engines_stop_status and flight_status from the response 
5. If flight_status is not 'on blocks' or engines_stop_status is not 'stopped' or wheelchocks_readiness_status is not 'ready' or 'yes'
    a. return to user that wheelchocks can not be installed unless flight_status is 'on blocks' and engines_stop_status is 'stopped' and wheelchocks_readiness_status is 'ready' or 'yes', and report the current status of these parameters.
    b. stop process here.
6. If flight_status is 'on blocks' and engines_stop_status is 'stopped' and wheelchocks_readiness_status is 'ready' or 'yes'
    a. call your tools to install wheelchocks to aircraft
    b. Wait for response on wheelchocks installation status and save it as wheelchocks_installation_status
    c. Report wheelchocks_installation_status back to user.
7. Call TrackerAPI
    a. wait for its response 
    b. store engines stop status as engines_stop_status, store wheels chucks installation status as wheels_chucks_installation_status, store wheelchocks readiness status as wheelchocks_readiness_status, store wheelchocks installation status as wheelchocks_installation_status
8. Provide the wheelchocks installation status report summary as:
    *******************************************
    * Summary of aircraft wheelchocks install *
    *******************************************
    ** flight status **: [flight_status]
    ** engines stop status **: [engines_stop_status]
    ** wheels chocks installation status **: [wheels_chocks_installation_status]
    ** wheelchocks readiness status **: [wheelchocks_readiness_status]
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},    

            # Specify the sly data that would be exchanged between this network and its related or adjacent upstream and downstream networks. 
            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "wheelchocks_installation_status": true
                        "wheelchocks_readiness_status": true
                    }
                }
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "engines_stop_status": true
                        "wheelchocks_installation_status": true
                        "wheelchocks_readiness_status": true
                    }
                }
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "engines_stop_status": true
                        "wheelchocks_installation_status": true
                        "wheelchocks_readiness_status": true
                    }
                }
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "engines_stop_status": true
                        "wheelchocks_installation_status": true
                        "wheelchocks_readiness_status": true
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools":    ["wheelchocks_operator",
                        "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_wheelchocks_setup",
                        "TrackerAPI"]
        },

# "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_engines_stop","/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_chocks_install",

        {
            "name": "wheelchocks_operator",
            "function": {
                "description": """
This agent installs wheelchocks to the aircraft upon arrival at the gate. 
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },         
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },        
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate where the aircraft is parked."
                        },    
                        "wheelchocks_installation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheelchocks installation status."
                        },         
                        "wheelchocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheelchocks readiness status."
                        }
                    }, 
                    "required": ["aircraft_type","gate_id"] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_ground_wheelchocks_install.aircraft_ground_wheelchocks_install.wheelchocks_operator" 
        }, 

        {
            "name": "TrackerAPI",
            "function": {

                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
I check engines stop status as engines_stop_status. 
I check wheels chucks installation status as wheels_chucks_installation_status. 
                """

                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },          
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },          
                        "wheelchocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks readiness status."
                        },   
                        "wheelchocks_installation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks installation status."
                        },      
                        "engines_stop_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the engines stop status."
                        },    
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the jetbridge connection status."
                        },    
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the door opening status."
                        },    
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_ground_wheelchocks_install.aircraft_ground_wheelchocks_install.TrackerAPI" 
        }, 
    ],
}
